[Episode 35]

4
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,680
Tell my wife

5
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,530
that the house is dirty,

6
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:50,310
so I don't want it anymore.

7
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,470
I'll get a new place.

8
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:52,229
Yes.

9
00:01:53,600 --> 00:02:02,840
[Enhancing Prosperity and Happiness]

10
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:59,150
This mansion has multiple courtyards.

11
00:01:59,789 --> 00:02:01,790
It is indeed magnificent, isn't it?

12
00:02:03,620 --> 00:02:05,240
[Loyalty]

13
00:02:06,390 --> 00:02:07,390
Isn't that Gu Yizhong?

14
00:02:07,390 --> 00:02:08,590
Yes, why is he here?

15
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:10,330
He's a big traitor.

16
00:02:10,350 --> 00:02:12,010
He's done so many evil things.

17
00:02:26,070 --> 00:02:26,990
In you go.

18
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:37,320
[Yuqing Hall]

19
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:37,110
But the chair…

20
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,380
is uncomfortable to sit in.

21
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:42,400
Madam, do you need us to change the furniture for you?

22
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:43,710
What do you know?

23
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:47,030
This is rosewood.

24
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:48,670
But it's okay.

25
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:49,790
Change it.

26
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:53,210
Go to Mr. Li's old place, the Crane Garden.

27
00:02:53,390 --> 00:02:54,270
In his living room,

28
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:55,670
there is a set of leather sofas.

29
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:56,530
Move them here.

30
00:02:56,790 --> 00:02:58,550
Remove

31
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,070
the hard furniture.

32
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:01,230
Now that we've won the war,

33
00:03:01,230 --> 00:03:02,510
the National Government of Chongqing

34
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:05,040
should settle accounts with these traitors.

35
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:10,910
Xia Guanghui. Li Yaoxian. Tang Jiemin.

36
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:11,600
Yes.

37
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:11,910
Yes.

38
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:12,310
Yes.

39
00:03:12,470 --> 00:03:13,670
The Military Commission has issued the order

40
00:03:13,670 --> 00:03:16,030
to free up this cell immediately.

41
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:17,030
From now on,

42
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:19,710
it will be a place to lock up traitors only.

43
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:20,550
Traitors?

44
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:25,430
This plaque, Yuqing Hall…

45
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,360
[Yuqing Hall]

46
00:03:25,790 --> 00:03:27,190
Take it off. I don't want it.

47
00:03:27,190 --> 00:03:27,710
Yes.

48
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:30,010
Two new safes will arrive tomorrow.

49
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:32,140
Tell them to send them here directly.

50
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:34,150
Put them in our bedroom.

51
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:35,150
Yes, Madam.

52
00:03:59,079 --> 00:03:59,670
Zhou.

53
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,910
I don't want to go back to Zhou's Mansion.

54
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:06,030
This place already is yours.

55
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:07,350
I'll have someone

56
00:04:07,460 --> 00:04:10,070
hang the plaque of Zhou's Mansion this afternoon.

57
00:04:10,070 --> 00:04:10,870
No, no, no.

58
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:14,010
Don't hang the plaque of Zhou's Mansion.

59
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:15,080
That's not good.

60
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,610
It's too flashy.

61
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:18,490
Let's change the name.

62
00:04:20,470 --> 00:04:21,510
Zhou's Garden.

63
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,390
Zhou's Garden.

64
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,060
Good!

65
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:24,990
Zhou's Garden!

66
00:04:26,230 --> 00:04:27,630
Did you set up the radio station?

67
00:04:27,630 --> 00:04:28,110
Yes.

68
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:31,510
I'll send a telegram to Chongqing.

69
00:04:32,030 --> 00:04:33,470
Take a walk around.

70
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,630
Don't get lost.

71
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,750
It's big here.

72
00:05:17,590 --> 00:05:18,230
Write.

73
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:24,160
Write what?

74
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,680
A confession statement.

75
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:30,070
Your name. Date of birth. Where are you from?

76
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,930
When did you become a traitor?

77
00:05:32,030 --> 00:05:33,960
How many people died in your hands?

78
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,200
Write them all down.

79
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,190
Sir.

80
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:44,810
Help me send a message.

81
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:47,830
You're already in this state,

82
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,750
and you're still thinking about sending a message?

83
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,110
Well…

84
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:52,350
Don't get me in trouble, Mr. Gu.

85
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:16,430
They'll pay you 100 yuan when they see this.

86
00:06:16,430 --> 00:06:18,590
To Dr. Lu Zhaohe from Zhaohe Hospital.

87
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:22,270
Here.

88
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:23,910
Thank you.

89
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,870
Hurry up and write the confession statement.

90
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:27,600
The higher-ups are rushing me.

91
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,320
What a coincidence.

92
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:32,240
In!

93
00:06:35,030 --> 00:06:36,230
Okay, thank you.

94
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:43,470
Oh no.

95
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,270
Something bad happened!

96
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,150
Monk Yiren.

97
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,150
We've won the war!

98
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:48,650
Don't scare me like that. Okay?

99
00:06:48,650 --> 00:06:50,770
Mr. Gu from Suzhou has been arrested.

100
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:51,900
Mr. Gu?

101
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:53,420
When did it happen?

102
00:06:53,530 --> 00:06:55,080
I just got the news.

103
00:06:58,350 --> 00:06:59,600
What should we do?

104
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:09,280
[Celebrate the Victory of the War of Resistance]

105
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,010
Why is there so much traffic today?

106
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:13,380
The official for the reception appointed by Chongqing

107
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:14,950
is working in the Gu's Garden.

108
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:17,150
These people are all going to his place to send gifts.

109
00:07:17,150 --> 00:07:18,410
It has lasted for days.

110
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:23,670
Let me take a walk inside.

111
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,190
Line up.

112
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:26,780
I just want to go inside Zhou's Garden for a minute.

113
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:27,550
Line up.

114
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:28,790
What line?

115
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:29,700
I'm going home.

116
00:07:30,170 --> 00:07:30,910
Line up.

117
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:33,320
This is the Gu's Garden. I'm Mrs. Gu.

118
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,430
Go away.

119
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:39,720
Please.

120
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:42,140
Goodness.

121
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:44,659
Thank you.

122
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:46,240
Alright, Chairman Gao.

123
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,320
Give the current situation, please be more understanding.

124
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,050
Don't worry.

125
00:07:49,090 --> 00:07:50,130
I'll speak for you

126
00:07:50,150 --> 00:07:51,310
in front of Mr. Dai.

127
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,290
Okay, thank you very much.

128
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,420
Zhou.

129
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,690
Look who's here.

130
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,130
Director Zhou.

131
00:08:05,010 --> 00:08:07,730
Zhang Haimo, Gu Yizhong's wife.

132
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:11,650
Hello, Miss Haimo.

133
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:14,330
Director Zhou.

134
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,580
I want to ask you about something.

135
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:17,310
Sir,

136
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:20,200
an emergency call from Chongqing.

137
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:21,900
Coming.

138
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:24,530
You guys talk first.

139
00:08:26,070 --> 00:08:27,300
Come on, Mrs. Gu.

140
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:30,950
Zhou

141
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:32,950
is really busy now.

142
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:36,350
Military Commission. Special Station.

143
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:37,750
Traitor-purging Commitee.

144
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,190
Three jobs!

145
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,990
He has to deal with three jobs at the same times.

146
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:42,960
Mrs. Zhou,

147
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:44,990
I just have one question.

148
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:48,910
Where is Gu Yizhong now?

149
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,140
Mr. Gu…

150
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:52,810
What?

151
00:08:53,070 --> 00:08:54,340
I thought Mr. Gu

152
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,510
had taken your whole family

153
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,310
to exile in Hong Kong.

154
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,440
We've been in Suzhou all this time.

155
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:03,910
Then, how can we know

156
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,600
where he is?

157
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,670
You really have to

158
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:11,390
tell him not to show up.

159
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:13,910
The public sentiment is surging.

160
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:15,030
It's chaotic.

161
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:18,590
If he was arrested as a traitor,

162
00:09:18,950 --> 00:09:21,150
I'm afraid even Zhou can't protect him.

163
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:25,870
Have you heard that

164
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:27,440
a few days ago,

165
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:30,170
Commissioner Yu of the Civil Affairs Bureau

166
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:33,540
was forced to jump into the river to commit suicide?

167
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,250
He was really panicked.

168
00:09:36,230 --> 00:09:37,630
I've asked Zhang Jiping.

169
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,180
He said

170
00:09:43,110 --> 00:09:44,270
it was Director Zhou

171
00:09:45,030 --> 00:09:47,400
who led a group to take Gu Yizhong away.

172
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:48,350
Nonsense!

173
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:50,350
Okay.

174
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:52,250
Mrs. Zhou,

175
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,440
please ask Zhou Zhifei to come here.

176
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,050
I'll ask him face-to-face.

177
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:58,540
What Zhou Zhifei?

178
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:04,070
My husband's name is Zhou Youren now.

179
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,000
Okay.

180
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:10,190
Mrs. Zhou Youren,

181
00:10:10,590 --> 00:10:12,070
please help me with this.

182
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:13,870
Now,

183
00:10:14,430 --> 00:10:16,160
I just want to see Gu Yizhong.

184
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:22,840
Mrs. Gu,

185
00:10:24,150 --> 00:10:25,750
I know what you came here for.

186
00:10:26,190 --> 00:10:27,510
Go back for now.

187
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:30,070
I'll ask Zhou when he is free.

188
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,930
If he really knows about this matter,

189
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:34,860
he will definitely help.

190
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:38,210
After all, we've been friends for so many years.

191
00:10:38,310 --> 00:10:38,990
Right?

192
00:10:53,470 --> 00:10:54,310
Mrs. Gu.

193
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:55,660
Mrs. Gu.

194
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:01,540
I'm from Zhaohe Hospital.

195
00:11:01,710 --> 00:11:03,640
Mr. Lu asked me to wait for you here.

196
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:04,150
Okay.

197
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,230
Dr. Lu.

198
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:12,100
Haimo.

199
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:13,930
You came at the right time.

200
00:11:14,230 --> 00:11:15,790
This is a note from Yizhong.

201
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:22,220
[Contact Luo Wuqiang] [I'm fine] [Pay 100 legal tenders to the letter deliverer]

202
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:24,580
Where is he?

203
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,750
The Third Prison of Suzhou High Court.

204
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,130
It is at Shizikou.

205
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:32,250
The one who brought the note out is a prison guard there.

206
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,870
Stop! Who are you?

207
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,240
My husband is locked inside.

208
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:42,870
Can I go in and visit him?

209
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:45,270
This is a special period. No visitors are allowed.

210
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:48,200
-Please make an exception.
-Go away! Leave!

211
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:49,310
I...

212
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:50,350
Go away!

213
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:54,670
Are you Ms. Haimo

214
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,070
from Feng Garden Story-telling Theatre?

215
00:11:56,070 --> 00:11:56,910
It's me.

216
00:11:57,230 --> 00:11:58,830
I've heard

217
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:01,320
the Northeast Beginning you sang.

218
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,640
You sang so well.

219
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:03,830
You are...

220
00:12:03,910 --> 00:12:05,170
Please give me a favor.

221
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:06,990
You,

222
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:09,470
go to No. 59, on the back street.

223
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,230
From their balcony on the third floor,

224
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,160
you can see the prison's backyard.

225
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:15,840
Many families of the prisoners are there.

226
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:20,480
We were the only honest people.

227
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:24,430
When we were traitors, we only focused on being traitors.

228
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:26,030
We didn't secretly communicate

229
00:12:26,030 --> 00:12:27,620
with Chongqing

230
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:30,900
and pretended to be an underground operative.

231
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:33,190
Time to go out.

232
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:35,910
Hurry up.

233
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:43,350
It's done.

234
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:44,870
You too, hurry up.

235
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:55,320
[Obedience, Responsibility, Diligence, Service]

236
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:55,390
One, two, one. One, two, one. One, two, one.

237
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,160
Come on. Those at the back, move forward.

238
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,430
Come on. Those at the behind, Keep up.

239
00:12:58,430 --> 00:12:59,110
Hurry up.

240
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,390
Halt.

241
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,080
Turn right.

242
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,330
Right here. Go in.

243
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:07,670
They're out!

244
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:08,670
Give me the money.

245
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,310
Junjie, do you see me?

246
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:13,100
Over here. Look over here.

247
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:16,910
I'm here, Junjie!

248
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:19,510
The kid is here too. Look!

249
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,840
I'm here. Look at me.

250
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:23,950
Dad!

251
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:26,840
I miss you.

252
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:27,750
Dad!

253
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,840
Look at me.

254
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,200
Look!

255
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,110
Yizhong.

256
00:13:57,910 --> 00:13:58,840
Gu Yizhong.

257
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:00,390
Yizhong!

258
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:08,070
Yizhong. Gu Yizhong! Gu Yizhong!

259
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,800
Yizhong!

260
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:19,530
Yizhong!

261
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,830
Gu Yizhong.

262
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:24,700
Yizhong.

263
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,350
Yizhong.

264
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:30,690
Haimo!

265
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:31,930
Haimo!

266
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:34,660
Yizhong, how are you?

267
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:37,230
How are you inside?

268
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,190
Where is Junsheng?

269
00:14:39,530 --> 00:14:40,840
You are not a traitor.

270
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:41,870
You are a good man.

271
00:14:41,870 --> 00:14:43,590
How can they lock you up?

272
00:14:43,710 --> 00:14:45,070
My note...

273
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:46,530
What?

274
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:48,150
Did you see my note?

275
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:48,950
What?

276
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,160
What are you saying?

277
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:51,910
I'm fine.

278
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:53,950
Get me an architecture book.

279
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,520
"The Ways to Build."

280
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:58,270
It's in the drawer of my desk.

281
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,710
Bring it in for me.

282
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:05,490
I will find someone to save you.

283
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:07,590
Mrs. Lu is taking care of Junsheng.

284
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:08,950
Don't worry.

285
00:15:09,020 --> 00:15:11,030
I will get you out.

286
00:15:11,190 --> 00:15:12,120
What did you say?

287
00:15:13,630 --> 00:15:14,560
I will.

288
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:17,550
Everyone, assemble!

